msContents.summary: A collection of prayers belonging to the Ashkenazi rite.

msItem.title: A collection of prayers belonging to the Ashkenazi rite.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 14; written lines: 13; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Initial words written in larger characters. Hair side and flesh side of the folios indistinguishable. Parts of the text written in red ink.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi square script, punctuated, of the 15th century.

binding.p: Post 1600. Black leather. Boxed. Spine: 'Prayers, Hymns, Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Brit. Mus. Reg. 16 A. I.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Presented to the British Museum by George II in 1757 as part of the Old Royal Library.
